⸻

Runtime invariants

These are the first rules to make executable.

PR-INV-001 — Separation theorem

The model does not hold canonical state.
Canonical state lives in the runtime.

PR-INV-002 — Output must be inspectable

Every response produces a structured ThoughtObject.

PR-INV-003 — No response without gate check

Every outbound answer must pass invariant checks.

PR-INV-004 — Continuity is externalized

Continuity is rebuilt from persisted state, not assumed inside the model.

PR-INV-005 — Model-agnostic orchestration

Pantheon runtime can swap model providers without changing doctrine.

