ThoughtObject schema

Start simple and rigid.

from dataclasses import dataclass, field
from typing import List, Dict, Optional
from datetime import datetime
import uuid

@dataclass
class ThoughtObject:
    id: str
    session_id: str
    created_at: str
    input_text: str
    assembled_context_hash: str
    model_provider: str
    model_name: str
    daemon_trace: List[str]
    invariants_passed: List[str]
    invariants_failed: List[str]
    confidence: float
    output_text: str
    action_items: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    tags: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    lineage_parent_id: Optional[str] = None
    metadata: Dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict)

    @staticmethod
    def new(session_id: str, input_text: str) -> "ThoughtObject":
        return ThoughtObject(
            id=str(uuid.uuid4()),
            session_id=session_id,
            created_at=datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),
            input_text=input_text,
            assembled_context_hash="",
            model_provider="",
            model_name="",
            daemon_trace=[],
            invariants_passed=[],
            invariants_failed=[],
            confidence=0.0,
            output_text=""
        )


⸻

Execution loop

Step 1 — Ingress

User sends input.

Runtime creates:
	•	request id
	•	session id
	•	fresh ThoughtObject

Step 2 — Context assembly

Pull:
	•	Pantheon doctrine files
	•	session summary
	•	recent ThoughtObjects
	•	relevant long-term memory
	•	optional retrieval chunks from repo/docs

Step 3 — Daemon chain

Each daemon transforms the request packet.

Example:
	•	Spider: “what is the structure?”
	•	Mirror: “what is inconsistent?”
	•	Hound: “what is risky or unsupported?”
	•	Dragonfly: “what broader frame matters?”

Step 4 — Model call

Compiled prompt packet goes to selected model.

Step 5 — Invariant gate

Check output for:
	•	contradiction
	•	unsupported confidence
	•	ethics failure
	•	missing required structure

If failed:
	•	revise once automatically
	•	or route to safe fallback format

Step 6 — Persist

Write final ThoughtObject and update session state.

Step 7 — Return

Respond to user with approved output.

